(42, 20, 23, 40, 22, 18, 18, 'Why tempt ye me?', 'Connection of Perception and Temptation', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' awareness of the intentions of those questioning him. The phrases ''perceived their craftiness'' and ''perceived their wickedness'' highlight his insight into their motives, while both conclude with the challenge, ''Why tempt ye me?''', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
