(42, 20, 23, 19, 95, 9, 9, 'tempt ye me', 'Temptation and Testing Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of temptation in both passages. Luke 20:23 addresses the act of tempting, while Psalms 95:9 recalls how the fathers tempted God and proved Him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 20, 23, 40, 16, 1, 1, 'tempt ye me', 'Temptation by Religious Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the act of tempting Jesus by religious leaders. In Luke, Jesus perceives their craftiness, while in Matthew, the Pharisees and Sadducees explicitly seek to tempt Him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
