(42, 20, 24, 40, 18, 28, 28, 'Cesar’s', 'Connection of Debt and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of financial obligation and authority. In Luke, the reference to ''Cesar’s'' emphasizes the power of the state, while in Matthew, the servant''s demand for ''an hundred pence'' illustrates personal debt and authority over fellow servants.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 20, 24, 40, 20, 2, 2, 'a penny', 'Connection of Monetary Themes', 'This connection highlights the concept of a ''penny'' in both passages, emphasizing its significance in transactions and agreements. Both verses illustrate the use of currency in the context of labor and authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 20, 24, 42, 2, 1, 1, 'Cesar’s', 'Connection of Caesar''s Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of Caesar in relation to taxation. The mention of Caesar in both contexts highlights the political and economic power he wielded during that time.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
