(42, 20, 24, 44, 25, 8, 12, 'Cesar', 'Connection of Authority and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority, as both passages reference ''Cesar'' in the context of legal judgment. In Luke, the mention of Cesar''s image on the penny emphasizes Roman authority, while in Acts, Paul appeals to Cesar''s judgment seat, asserting his rights under that authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
